{"word":"πόριμος","slug":"πόριμος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πόριμος</b></el> <el>(πόρῐμος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πόρος'><el>πόρος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>able to provide, full of resources, inventive, contriving</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>ἄπορα πόριμος</el> <i>making possible</i> the impossible, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>practicable</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>well-provided</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}